The paper discusses data quality assessment, which is a topic closely related to databases (cs.DB). The use of ontologies and rules for representing dimensional constraints and doing query answering suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of Datalog+-, a logic programming language commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and software engineering (cs.SE) for representing and querying data.
